<paragraph id="CA39568BCF3643BB8B8D908CF8A3CA86" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="348BCB862F3C10E39F78B2B7091142EB" authorityName="Barboza" authorityYear="2011" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Capsicum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="6" pageNumber="29" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="eximium" status="nom. nov.">Capsicum eximium</taxonomicName>
var. 
<emphasis id="EDDC1F50C123A0E2A6E10ED3B6DBAAAF" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">tomentosum</emphasis>
Eshbaugh &amp; P.G.Sm., Baileya 18: 15. 1971, non 
<taxonomicName id="448D7B39A9C411A2D366D95EAE7C467A" authorityName="Barboza" authorityYear="2011" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Capsicum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="6" pageNumber="29" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tomentosum" status="nom. nov.">Capsicum tomentosum</taxonomicName>
Kuntze, 1891. - Holotype: BOLIVIA, Dpto. Santa Cruz, Prov. Florida, Mairana area, 1300 m, P.G.Smith Sa281 (holotype, IND!; isotypes: MU! (MU-153648, MU-153649). 
<figureCitation id="97A97CC7EEB809DFE8F489E122A54E52" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Capsicum eshbaughii. A embryo B, H, F, J, L glandular trichomes C fruit D non-glandular trichome E flowering branch G flower I gynoecium K seed M open corolla N fruiting calyx. Line drawing by P. Peralta; voucher A, C, K, N Nee 36164; B, D-J, L, M Eshbaugh 1943 b." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/9860" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
